  "answer": "**1. In-Depth User Understanding:** Understanding the human tendency to question the unknown, the scriptures explicitly emphasize that the precise timing of the Last Day is completely hidden from mankind. Surah Luqman 31:34 directly addresses this by stating that God alone possesses the exact knowledge of the Hour [1].\n\n**2. Robust and Enduring Framework:** This establishes a steadfast theological framework demonstrating that ultimate knowledge of the unseen belongs exclusively to the Creator. Surah Al-A'raf 7:187 reinforces this resilient foundation by commanding the Prophet to declare that knowledge of the Hour's arrival is solely with his Lord, and no one else will reveal its time [2], [3].\n\n**3. Elegant and Lucid Presentation:** The Quran elegantly and clearly warns that the Last Day will arrive suddenly. Surah Muhammad 47:18 lucidly presents this reality by asking if the disbelievers merely await the Hour to come upon them unexpectedly, confirming that some of its indications have already appeared [4].\n\n**4. Seamless and Accessible Experience:** This divine guidance seamlessly directs individuals toward an accessible path of spiritual readiness rather than vain speculation. By establishing that the Hour will not come except unexpectedly and that it lays heavily upon the heavens and the earth, believers are easily guided to remain constantly prepared for its arrival [3].",
